{
  "stem": "20142.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If there were shots that I heard, I don't remember, because there was constantly shooting by Germans, even at night, just to make sure that there is everything-- you know, in the evening, there was quiet.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was not a quiet.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Germans were shooting constantly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I would like to mention to you that they ignited number of houses.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the ghetto started to slowly burn.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Polish people were seeing this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were saying, this is the end of the Jewish community in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "However, when the uprising started on the April 19th, this was a different story, because they knew that-- they heard the shots and they knew the Germans exaggerated quite a bit by saying that in a day or two, the ghetto will fall.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The ghetto did not fall until some six weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was at first of the bunker of Anielewicz.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then I was at the bunker of [INAUDIBLE] Street 4.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was one of the bunkers that we were using on the way to Nalewki Street, then Antek Zuckerman bunkers.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was like a stopover or if necessary asking for help.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or even there was no need for any help to obtain, we continue without exposing any evidence that there is a bunker.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had to be very, very careful with this situation, because they were always another pair of eyes that were seeing.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And for the sake of [INAUDIBLE], trying to save the life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was on my way to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] with one of the messages from Anielewicz to Antek Zuckerman.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I heard the fighting and the rumbling tanks- and-- then I knew that we have to put up quite a bit of effort.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I returned the Mila 18 headquarter.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
